{
  "stem": "7598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I just wanted to add this, that my father-- my mother turned around and said, do you know what happened to my parents?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, yes, they were sent to a camp, but I think they were too old to work, and we haven't heard from them since.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father touched my mother and said, the child is overawed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She doesn't know what she's talking about.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And only when my brother confirmed it, that they were in deep shock.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think that things were just too horrific to really believe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The young cousin who helped us across to Paris and who eventually got to Switzerland, his parents were arrested in a raid on a train between Antwerp and Brussels.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the mother wrote a postcard from [NON-ENGLISH], which is where the train was stopped.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when he stopped hearing from them, he wrote a letter to Mr. and Mrs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He said, he had no-- I knew it was a work camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And his parents were in their late 40s.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He said even in Switzerland, they couldn't believe-- they knew, but they blocked it out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They just couldn't believe in 1943, even then, that they-- that it--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What happened.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My uncle and aunt and the two daughters couldn't get a visa on the strength of the entry visa to Bolivia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they finally purchased a transit visa through Spain and eventually got to Lisbon about three or four months after we did, that is, in October, 1942.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Unfortunately, my uncle was over 40, so he was too old to volunteer to fight in England.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Therefore, he didn't get an entry visa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the Belgian Congo, which belonged to Belgium, allowed him in, so they spent the war years in the Belgian Congo.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
